'''Claussen House''', also known as the Howard-Harllee-Claussen House, is a historic [[Plantation house in the Southern United States|plantation house]] located at [[Florence, South Carolina|Florence]], [[Florence County, South Carolina]].  It was built about 1830, and is a raised cottage with early-19th century [[Greek Revival architecture]] and late-19th century [[Italianate architecture|Italianate]] style alterations and additions.  Also on the property are a contributing [[smoke house]], gardener's cottage, hothouse/greenhouse, [[chicken coop]]/[[outhouse]], and carriage shed.<ref name = nrhpinv>{{Cite web | author = F. Preston Wilson| title =Claussen House| work = National Register of Historic Places - Nomination and Inventory | date = July 2000| url = http://www.nationalregister.sc.gov/florence/S10817721005/S10817721005.pdf | format = pdf | accessdate = 5 July 2012}}</ref><ref name = scdah>{{Cite web | title = Claussen House, Florence County (5109 Old River Rd., Florence)| work = National Register Properties in South Carolina | publisher = South Carolina Department of Archives and History  | url = http://www.nationalregister.sc.gov/florence/S10817721005/index.htm | accessdate = 5 July 2012}}</ref>

It was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 2001.<ref name = nris/>

